column6: This category represents slots fraction where the processor's Frontend undersupplies its Backend...
This metric represents slots fraction the Memory subsystem within the Backend was a bottleneck...
This metric represents slots fraction where Core non-memory issues were of a bottleneck...
This metric estimates how often the CPU was stalled without loads missing the L1 data cache...
This metric estimates cycles fraction the CPU performance was potentially limited due to Core computation issues (non divider-related)...
This metric estimates how often CPU was stalled due to store memory accesses...
This metric represents cycles fraction where the Divider unit was active...
This metric represents slots fraction the CPU was stalled due to Frontend latency issues...
This metric represents cycles fraction the CPU was stalled due to instruction cache misses...
This metric represents cycles fraction the CPU was stalled due to Branch Resteers...
This category represents slots fraction wasted due to incorrect speculations...
This metric represents cycles fraction the CPU was stalled due to instruction TLB misses...
This metric represents slots fraction the CPU was retiring uops fetched by the Microcode Sequencer (MS) unit...
This metric estimates the fraction of cycles when the CPU was stalled due to switches of uop delivery to the Microcode Sequencer (MS)...
This metric represents Core cycles fraction in which CPU was likely limited due to the MITE pipeline (Legacy Decode Pipeline)...
This category represents slots fraction where no uops are being delivered due to a lack of required resources for accepting new uops in the Backend...
This metric represents cycles fraction the CPU was stalled due to switches from DSB to MITE pipelines...
